ratings:
(4â­) Everything is good. The best cafÃ© in Othaim Mall ğŸ˜. Recommended ğŸ‘ - 4 years ago | (1â­) VERY BAD CUSTOMER SERVICE

Everyday I visit Oliver Brown cafe, usually during the after noon, the employees there are very welcoming during this time.

Today, I went to the cafe in the morning at about 10 am, it was closed and no one was there knowing that it usually opens about 8 to 9 am. I waited for about one hour and no one came. I went to a near coffee shop and I bought coffee.

After about half an hour the employee came, and she starting saying that we cannot drink our coffee there. So I ordered from her 2 cups  but she was very rude and she treated us very badly. She was insisting on us to buy desert from her otherwise we cannot stay. Also she said that we had to stay at the cafe from where we bought the coffee from, so we left.

Unfortunatly, it is my last time for me visiting this cafe.

I was extremely disappointed with this experience and the way that we got treated.

I strongly advise to seek for another cafe nearby to have a pleasant and enjoyable experience.

Its truly a shame that such a beuitiful space is marred by such a customer service experience. - a year ago | (2â­) I love their mugs , actually bought 2 to add to my collection. ( 2 stars for the coffee mugs)

name: Snow City
ratings:
(5â­) A Winter Wonderland in the Desert: Snow City, Al Othaim Mall

If youâ€™re looking for a fun and unique family adventure in Riyadh, Snow City at Al Othaim Mall is a must-visit. As a family living in the desert, we couldnâ€™t resist the idea of stepping into a winter wonderland for a couple of hoursâ€”and it did not disappoint!

A Personal, Exclusive Experienceâ€¦
We visited Snow City during a quiet time and had the entire park to ourselves, which made the experience feel intimate and extra special. Spending two hours surrounded by snow and engaging in a variety of activities turned out to be the perfect amount of time. At 169 SAR per person, I initially thought it was a little pricey for a family of four, but as we explored ride after ride, it became clear that the experience was worth every riyal.

Thrills for Everyoneâ€¦
Snow City has a great mix of activities for kids and adults alike. The rides and slides are not just for small children; theyâ€™re designed to be exciting and memorable for all ages. From tobogganing to riding rubber rings and even navigating a luge, every slide offered something new. My daughters especially loved the snow plough bumper cars and the snowmobilesâ€”watching them zoom around with big smiles on their faces was a highlight for me.

Another standout activity was the climbing wall. Unlike a traditional rock wall, this one had handle-style grips, making it accessible to everyone. Reaching the top and rappelling down with the auto-belay was thrilling, and we all had multiple turns. Itâ€™s a little more physical than you might expectâ€”climbing, crawling, and sliding keep you activeâ€”but that only added to the fun.

Impeccable Facilitiesâ€¦
The attention to cleanliness and organization was impressive. Snow suits, boots, gloves, and helmets were provided and looked brand new. Even the socks they gave us were fresh out of the package! The changing rooms were spotless, and the equipment inside the park was clearly well-maintained. The snow itself was clean and fluffyâ€”perfect for snowball fights and making snow angels.

Fantastic Staff and Serviceâ€¦
The staff truly made our experience unforgettable. Because the park was empty, they gave us their full attention, ensuring we felt welcome, safe, and well looked after. They carefully explained the rules for each activity, especially the climbing wall, and their cheerful demeanor made the experience even more enjoyable. The kids felt especially special thanks to their kindness and encouragement.

A Unique Desert Escapeâ€¦
Snow City offers a unique escape from the desert heat. Playing in the snow, exploring the igloo maze, and having a snowball fight felt surrealâ€”and so much fun. By the end of the two hours, we were all tired, exhilarated, and a little chilly, but we left with warm hearts and great memories.

Tips for Visitingâ€¦
We recommend visiting during quieter times to fully enjoy the park without crowds. Weâ€™ve been during both the Christmas holidays and Ramadan, and both visits were equally peaceful. Look out for special offers during the year to save on ticket prices.

While 169 SAR per person might seem steep at first, the exclusive feel, pristine facilities, and variety of activities made it worthwhile. For us, two hours was just the right amount of time before toes started freezing!

Final Thoughtsâ€¦
Snow City is perfect for families with kids around 8-11 years old, but adults will have plenty of fun too. Itâ€™s an active, exhilarating experience that offers something rare and special in Riyadhâ€”a chance to play in the snow in the middle of the desert.

We walked away with a shared family memory that weâ€™ll cherish for years. For anyone looking for a fun, active, and memorable day out, Snow City is a winter wonderland worth exploring. - 2 months ago | (5â­) We reached their at 2 pm on sunday and there was no queue, we purchased card and went inside to take clothes, helmet, gloves etc then entered the main snow area by swapping card. There was only single family inside at that time.

My daughter two and half years old had loose shoes, so she was not able to walk properly. She was also feeling cold even after wearing the dress given by them. So, after a while my wife and daughter went outside and I and my elder daughter were inside.

There were multiple activities to do inside, like sliding down in a tube, dodging car, snow house to play hide n seek, a large slide which needs a board to sleep on and slide into the snow and more.
